We used to see this occasionally on EC2 when there was significant IO - etcd writes frequently to disk, and would miss heartbeats when there's significant IO activity preventing its writes from occurring within a reasonable time.

Moving the Docker graph to its own EBS volume and moving the etcd snapshot directory to the fast ephemeral disk on EC2 virtually eliminated etcd/fleet issues on EC2.

