I think that covers all uses of `require` in this repo. As for providing a _simple_ way for extensions authors/maintainers to do the same, here's a sampling of `require` usage across many extensions: https://github.com/ipython-contrib/jupyter_contrib_nbextensions/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=require&type=

The patterns looks like:

```js
define([ 'require' ], function(require) {
  ...
})
```

In some (including the cookiecutters), there is also:

```js
/**
 * Configure requirejs.
 */
if (window.require) {
  window.require.config({
    map: {
      '*': {
        'jupyterlab_json': 'nbextensions/jupyterlab_json/index'
      }
    }
  });
}
```

So replacing `require` with `requirejs` in those contexts should cover most cases. If we want to provide a comprehensive solution, we can use [jscodeshift](https://github.com/facebook/jscodeshift) which uses and AST-based approach. Here's an example of a codemod that replaces `require` statements with `import` statements: https://github.com/cpojer/js-codemod/blob/master/transforms/rm-requires.js

