@jmetz not sure if there is any written guideline.
I believe that the granularity of the _merged_ commits has to be strongly dependent on the way the project is being developed and maintained. We almost never revert commits, neither we have a high PR/month ratio. Saying this, I think that the best approach could be to split all the commits from a PR into the largest possible atomic changes.
More concrete, I'd squash the commits in this PR into 1 (prefered), at most 2.

